    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just not even about \"being myself\" though. there's no \"self\" left when everyone sees you as a criminal or a failure. the person i was is dead. coming back from this feels like trying to rebuild a skyscraper out of dust. it doesn't make sense to keep trying to fix something that's fundamentally broken beyond repair.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
